   Date: Sat, 21 Nov 87 23:03:58 EST
   From: "Philip A. Prindeville" &lt;PAP4@ai.ai.mit.edu&gt;

   What about setting up MX records for *.BITNET to go to these gateways?
   One still has to explicitly route mail on the Internet to the correct
   gateways...

   -Philip

This has been discussed before, and is an improper use of the domain
naming system. Instead, there should be MX records for hosts on Bitnet
that reflect the organization that the host is in, instead of the
network the host is on.

For example, "cunyvm.bitnet" really should be something like
"vm.cuny.edu", with an MX pointing it to the appropriate gateway. 

